bug.short_desc: [POG] data doesn't collected after reatach in hybrid scenario

long_desc.thetext:
Build ID: 3.4
Steps To Reproduce: 1. deploy tomcat 2. run squiggle browser. java.exe -cp . -agentlib:JPIBootLoader=JPIAgent:server=enabled;CGProf:execdetails=true -jar batik-squiggle.jar
and browse URL (http://localhost:8080/jsp-examples/jsp2/jspx/textRotate.jspx?name=TPTP_Sample) 3. run WB 4. Attach to batik, gather some data 5. Detach from squiggle and wait some time 6. Reatach to squiggle 7. Reload URL in squiggle ("name" option in URL can be changed) problem happens from time to time

Adding comments from the wiki;
If the workbench detaches from an agent or clears all data in memory, the agent does not resend any missing data needed by the workbench in order to continue. No additional protocol should be added to the agent for this use case but an attach or reattach scenario should cause the agent to send fresh data as needed. For example the agent can keep track of what class definitions it has sent and send them if not previously done. A detach should simply clear this log of data sent so the agent just starts over.

I can't reproduce this defect using last 4.5 dev. build. After reattaching all data looks good, all tables populated, no NPE thrown, no unknown methods. I reattached from the same workspace as well as from other clean.
The only problem was found - performance degradation of profiled application (squiggle browser) in aggregative collecting mode. In this mode profiling agent sends all collected data it has every 10 seconds. It seems that only data delta should be send. I'm going to open new bugzilla to track this.

This is what I had done to setup the use case: 1. Download Tomcat 5.5 and unzip it to my local machine, go to Tomcat/bin and run startup.bat 2. Once server is started, load the main page(http:localhost:8080) and follow "JSP Example">"SVG (Scalable Vector Graphics)" and click on the "Execute" link. 3. JSP 2.0 SVG Example is opened in browser. Read the content and follow its instruction to: a. download batik. b. unzip batik to my local machine. 4. Once batik is unpacked to my local machine, start the squiggle browser with profiling agent: a. setup environement: Set TPTP_AC_HOME=D:\TPTPAgentController set JAVA_PROFILER_HOME=%TPTP_AC_HOME%\plugins\org.eclipse.tptp.javaprofiler Set PATH=%JAVA_PROFILER_HOME%;%PATH%;%TPTP_AC_HOME%\bin Set PATH=%PATH%;%JAVA_HOME%\bin b. start broswer: java -cp . -agentlib:JPIBootLoader=JPIAgent:server=enabled;CGProf:execdetails=true -jar batik-squiggle.jar 5. Attach from TPTP workbench to the java process (add filter to include org.apache* and exclude everything else), start monitoring 6. Put the sampel URL in Squiggle browser, ie http://localhost:8080/jsp-examples/jsp2/jspx/textRotate.jspx?name=JSPX. Note there is exception throw but there is still data collected. 7. See data collected and shown in Execution Statistic view. 8. Detach process from workbench. 9. Attach to process from workbench again, start monitoring. 10.Invoke the URL again. 11.Nothing is shown in the Execution Statistic view.
I would like to raise this to critical/blocker.
Eugene, can you reproduce this problem with Sun JVM?
Eugene, I'm unable to reproduce this using IBM JVM 1.5 SR 6 and Sun JVM 1.5. Also please correct your use case since "execdetails" option is currently not supported when running in "enabled" mode.

Hi Igor, I can reproduce the problem with both IBM JVM 1.5 SR6 and SUN JVM 1.5_11 build.
When I launch the squiggle broswer with SUN JVM: D:\java_sun_1.5.0_11\jre\bin\java.exe -cp . -agentlib:JPIBootLoader=JPIAgent:server=enabled;CGProf -jar batik-squiggle.jar The problem mentioned in item 3 of comment #5 does not shown. The browser problem only shows when the browser is launched with IBM JVM.
On the other hand, I see a weird behavior when reattach to agent in profiling monitor view: first, when reattach using the context menu action of agent(agent1) > "Attach to Agent", a new agent(agent2) is created in profiling monitor view and it does not collect any data. second, if I detach the agent(agent2), and reattach using the Profile Configuration > "Attach to Agent", select the detached agent and click "Profile" to attach and trace, a new agent(agent3) is created and there is data collected but data are collected to both agent2 and agent3. Please see screen capture. This problem happens to both IBM and SUN JVMs.
Created attachment 96493 screen capture of problem.

Hi Eugene, the reattach scenario works well for me with last TPTP build 200804231524 and Sun jvm. Blocking deffect in the comment #9 was fixed with rolling back of the patch #223385. Can you please check whether your problems remain?

I can reproduce the problem with tptp.sdk-TPTP-4.5.0-200804280100 with IBM JVM. The problem does NOT exist with Sun JVM 1.5.
Also when the Squiggle browser with IBM JVM, after I reattach to the profiling agent, I note that if I open the launch configuration again I can see the attached agent is still listed in the agent list available for attach. This is wrong and the agent once attached shouldn't be listed in the agent list for attach again. This could be a missing in update on the agent status after attached.
Hi Eugene, what remaining problem with IBM jvm do you mean? Initial issue - data are not collected after reattach. Or issue with DOMException (Comment 5, pont 3)?

(In reply to comment #13) > Hi Eugene, what remaining problem with IBM jvm do you mean? > Initial issue - data are not collected after reattach. > Or issue with DOMException (Comment 5, pont 3)? > Both IBM JVM not collecting and DOMException problem.

I had an e-meeting with Alex, and it seems like if I wait enough time after detach action is performed to allow the detach process to finish first, before I reattach to the same process, I can get profiling data collected. This is a timing issue that needs to be solved. Perhaps the detach complete notification shouldn't be sent to to the client for status update until the detach process is actually finished, which can stop user from reattaching also.
The DOMException problem is also reproducible on Alex's machine.
Alex, would you please open separate defects to track these problems separately as discussed.

Two records are opened as requested: Bug 231036 Bug 231037
